name: The Deck
description: The main canteen for the Faculty of Arts and Social Sciences, situated on a hill with distinctive architecture. Famous for its long-queue Yong Tau Foo and roasted delights.

name: Frontier
description: The Science faculty canteen offering a breezy, open-air environment. Popular for its Western food, Ayam Penyet, and Hainanese Chicken Rice.

name: Techno Edge
description: The primary canteen for the Faculty of Engineering. Features a diverse range of affordable stalls including popular Nasi Padang and Indian cuisine.

name: The Terrace
description: Located between the Business School and School of Computing. A busy lunch spot known for its Western food, Duck Rice, and Vietnamese noodles.

name: Fine Food
description: An air-conditioned food court in Town Plaza, UTown. Offers a wide variety of cuisines including Mala Xiang Guo, Korean, and Dim Sum.

name: Flavours @ UTown
description: The second air-conditioned food court in UTown, located at Stephen Riady Centre. A student favorite for mixed rice, fishball noodles, and local favorites.

name: PGP Canteen
description: Located within the Prince George's Park Residences. A go-to spot for residents offering late-night supper options, intense Mala, and Western grills.

name: Yusof Ishak House (YIH) Food Court
description: Centrally located at Yusof Ishak House. A convenient air-conditioned stop near the central library, featuring vegetarian options and bubble tea.

name: Hwang's Korean Restaurant
description: A casual, authentic Korean eatery in UTown. Extremely popular for its affordable spicy pork, bibimbap, and kimchi pancakes.

name: Waa Cow!
description: A specialty Japanese beef bowl restaurant in UTown. Famous for its premium flame-torched Wagyu beef bowls and onsen eggs.

name: SuperSnacks
description: A late-night savory snack counter in UTown. The ultimate supper spot for students craving crispy waffles, nuggets, and fries while studying.

name: The Royals Bistro
description: A Halal-certified bistro in UTown serving Western cuisine, pasta, and cakes. A comfortable spot for casual dining or meetings.

name: Udon Don Bar
description: A Japanese noodle bar in UTown offering fresh Udon and Donburi bowls. A cozy air-conditioned venue for a hearty Japanese meal.

name: Reedz Cafe
description: A quiet cafe located in the Mochtar Riady Building. serves freshly brewed coffee, sandwiches, and pastries, ideal for quick bites between classes.

name: Starbucks (UTown)
description: A popular 24-hour study spot (outdoor seating) and meeting point in UTown, serving the standard range of coffee, frappuccinos, and pastries.

name: Burnt Cones
description: A premium gelato and waffle cafe at Yusof Ishak House. Known for its distinct ice cream flavors and crispy, buttery cones.
